The paper deals with constructing a spanner over a set of points in $\mathbb{R}^d$ that is resilient to catastrophic failure of nodes. This problem is related to topics such as data structures, computational geometry, numerical analysis, distributed computing, and social networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
